---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — notiq" description="Why we built notiq">
  <Header />
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pt-20 sm:pt-24 pb-20 sm:pb-24">

    <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-orange-500 mb-5">About</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink dark:text-zinc-50 mb-6 leading-tight">
      We got tired of gluing together<br />six notification libraries.
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-muted dark:text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-10">
      Every Python app eventually needs notifications. You start with one email, then SMS, then in-app alerts.
      Suddenly you have three separate provider SDKs, three sets of credentials, and triple the maintenance surface.
      That's exactly the problem notiq was built to solve.
    </p>

    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-14">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border dark:border-zinc-800 bg-paper dark:bg-zinc-900 p-6">
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-ink dark:text-zinc-100 mb-2">The problem</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted dark:text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          Notification infrastructure is one of those things every app needs but nobody wants to rebuild from scratch.
          You end up with fragile glue code that breaks when providers change their APIs.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border dark:border-zinc-800 bg-paper dark:bg-zinc-900 p-6">
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-ink dark:text-zinc-100 mb-2">Our bet</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted dark:text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          One Python SDK with a clean interface should be enough to send notifications everywhere.
          Swap providers without touching your application code.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-border dark:border-zinc-800 pt-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink dark:text-zinc-50 mb-3">Open source forever</h2>
      <p class="text-muted dark:text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed text-sm mb-6 max-w-lg">
        notiq is MIT licensed — self-host for full control.
        Use our hosted service if you want zero ops. Either way, you're never locked in.
      </p>
      <a href="https://github.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
         class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-2 rounded-lg border border-border dark:border-zinc-700 text-ink dark:text-zinc-200 hover:border-orange-400 hover:text-orange-500 dark:hover:border-orange-500 transition-colors">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
          <path d="M12 0C5.374 0 0 5.373 0 12c0 5.302 3.438 9.8 8.207 11.387.599.111.793-.261.793-.577v-2.234c-3.338.726-4.033-1.416-4.033-1.416-.546-1.387-1.333-1.756-1.333-1.756-1.089-.745.083-.729.083-.729 1.205.084 1.839 1.237 1.839 1.237 1.07 1.834 2.807 1.304 3.492.997.107-.775.418-1.305.762-1.604-2.665-.305-5.467-1.334-5.467-5.931 0-1.311.469-2.381 1.236-3.221-.124-.303-.535-1.524.117-3.176 0 0 1.008-.322 3.301 1.23A11.509 11.509 0 0 1 12 5.803c1.02.005 2.047.138 3.006.404 2.291-1.552 3.297-1.23 3.297-1.23.653 1.653.242 2.874.118 3.176.77.84 1.235 1.911 1.235 3.221 0 4.609-2.807 5.624-5.479 5.921.43.372.823 1.102.823 2.222v3.293c0 .319.192.694.801.576C20.566 21.797 24 17.3 24 12c0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12z"/>
        </svg>
        View on GitHub
      </a>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
